I"F	<p>The evening we had a presentation about “Panoramic photography”. A variety of styles and techniques were shown, the use of the tripod was emphasised when using the camera. However, it was also pointed out that some cameras’ provide a ‘Panorama’ option amongst their facilities. We then went onto software options – a demonstration of proprietary and various free to download software was made. </p>

<p><em>Members receive a copy of the presentation in the club newsletter.</em></p>

<p><br /></p>

<hr />

<p><br /></p>

<p>The ‘Monthly Competition’ entitled <em>‘Market Day’</em> was held.</p>

<p>The winners were:-</p>

<ul>
	<li>1st - 'Oil, try it' by John Horton</li>
	<li>2nd - 'Ludlow 1' by Julie Beddow</li>
	<li>2nd - 'Ludlow 2' by Julie Beddow</li>
	<li>2nd - 'Telford Christmas Market' y John Wilkinson</li>
	<li>3rd - 'Saturday Market' by John Horotn</li>
</ul>

